 \"to\": 3101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2992, \"end\": 2997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999951208884226, \"rank\": 4.879135218765264e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his work\", \"from\": 2916, \"to\": 2924}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2954}, {\"ngram\": \"Maximus\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 2964}, {\"ngram\": \"human flesh\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3017}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 3042, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"the renewal\", \"from\": 3069, \"to\": 3080}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire world\", \"from\": 3084, \"to\": 3100}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the Last Supper, Jesus' act of celebrating communion signified that just as the bread and wine are transformed by faith into His body and blood, He would also transform the heavens and the earth.\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3304, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3126, \"end\": 3131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999951208884226, \"rank\": 4.879135218765264e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"communion\", \"from\": 3152, \"to\": 3161}, {\"ngram\": \"the bread\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3194}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3203}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3228}, {\"ngram\": \"His body\", \"from\": 3234, \"to\": 3242}, {\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3252}, {\"ngram\": \"the heavens\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3289}, {\"ngram\": \"the earth\", \"from\": 3294, \"to\": 3303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(See Maximus's view of the incarnationhere.)\", \"from\": 3306, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Maximus's view\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3325}, {\"ngram\": \"the incarnationhere\", \"from\": 3329, \"to\": 3348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When believers partake in communion (the Eucharist), it is not a mere ritual.\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3393, \"end\": 3402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.263120882736345e-18, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"believers\", \"from\": 3357, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"communion\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is a profound act of faith, symbolizing their fellowship with Jesus, marking their covenant to serve Him, overcome worldly systems, and join in the renewal of all things (Isaiah 65:17; Revelation 21:1-8).\", \"from\": 3430, \"to\": 3637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999951208884226, \"rank\": 4.879135218765264e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a profound act\", \"from\": 3436, \"to\": 3450}, {\"ngram\": \"faith\", \"from\": 3454, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"their fellowship\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"their covenant\", \"from\": 3510, \"to\": 3524}, {\"ngram\": \"worldly systems\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3563}, {\"ngram\": \"the renewal\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3588}, {\"ngram\": \"all things\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3602}, {\"ngram\": \"Isaiah\", \"from\": 3604, \"to\": 3610}, {\"ngram\": \"Revelation\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3628}, {\"ngram\": \"21:1-8)\", \"from\": 3629, \"to\": 3636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This commitment reflects their dedication to participate in the cosmic renewal promised by Christ.\", \"from\": 3638, \"to\": 3736, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This commitment\", \"from\": 3638, \"to\": 3653}, {\"ngram\": \"their dedication\", \"from\": 3663, \"to\": 3679}, {\"ngram\": \"the cosmic renewal\", \"from\": 3698, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 3729, \"to\": 3735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In my view, the blasphemous depiction of drag queens mimicking the Last Supper was a bold statement by the Olympic producers, in collaboration with Euro Globalists, signaling their intent to reshape the world in their distorted image.\", \"from\": 3738, \"to\": 3972, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my view\", \"from\": 3741, \"to\": 3748}, {\"ngram\": \"the blasphemous depiction\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3775}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3790}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3816}, {\"ngram\": \"a bold statement\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3837}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic producers\", \"from\": 3841, \"to\": 3862}, {\"ngram\": \"collaboration\", \"from\": 3867, \"to\": 3880}, {\"ngram\": \"Euro Globalists\", \"from\": 3886, \"to\": 3901}, {\"ngram\": \"their intent\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 3925}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3937, \"to\": 3946}, {\"ngram\": \"their distorted image\", \"from\": 3950, \"to\": 3971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This act symbolically declares that the new world order they envision seeks to systematically dismantle the Judeo-Christian values that have underpinned Western civilization for over a millennium.\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 4169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4081, \"end\": 4103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Judeo-Christian values\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judeo-Christian_ethics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This act\", \"from\": 3973, \"to\": 3981}, {\"ngram\": \"the new world order\", \"from\": 4009, \"to\": 4028}, {\"ngram\": \"Western civilization\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4146}, {\"ngram\": \"a millennium\", \"from\": 4156, \"to\": 4168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This strategic move highlights their agenda to overturn the moral and cultural foundations that have shaped Europe and the Western nations for centuries.\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4293, \"end\": 4300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.766367723662015e-16, \"text\": \"Western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This strategic move\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4189}, {\"ngram\": \"their agenda\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4213}, {\"ngram\": \"the moral and cultural foundations\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4260}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 4278, \"to\": 4284}, {\"ngram\": \"centuries\", \"from\": 4313, \"to\": 4322}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the first 600 years of the Church, Christians infiltrated every facet of society, ultimately dismantling the pagan gods of the Roman and Greco cultures.\", \"from\": 4325, \"to\": 4480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4363, \"end\": 4373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999991265989768, \"rank\": 8.734021611188696e-07, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 4455, \"end\": 4460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.5857109527143151, \"rank\": 0.7052738715580509, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the first 600 years\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4347}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 4351, \"to\": 4361}, {\"ngram\": \"every facet\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4397}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4408}, {\"ngram\": \"the pagan gods\", \"from\": 4433, \"to\": 4447}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apostolic pioneers like Saint Patrick and Saint Boniface ventured into pagan strongholds such as Ireland and Germany.\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4598, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4511, \"end\": 4518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7324277154936284e-26, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 4523, \"end\": 4537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Boniface\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.425654444918915e-56, \"text\": \"Saint Boniface\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Boniface\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Boniface\"}, {\"begin\": 4552, \"end\": 4557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1343707246269842e-14, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 4578, \"end\": 4585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9713040861053186, \"rank\": 0.02953878598898191, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 4590, \"end\": 4597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.8302256346770005, \"rank\": 0.20426448849073423, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Apostolic pioneers\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They challenged the reigning deities and demonstrated the supremacy of Jesus Christ by triumphing over demonically inspired priests and pagan clergy in power encounters.\", \"from\": 4599, \"to\": 4768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4670, \"end\": 4682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999966699107031, \"rank\": 3.3301001811237196e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 4735, \"end\": 4740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1343707246269842e-14, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reigning deities\", \"from\": 4615, \"to\": 4635}, {\"ngram\": \"the supremacy\", \"from\": 4653, \"to\": 4666}, {\"ngram\": \"demonically inspired priests\", \"from\": 4702, \"to\": 4730}, {\"ngram\": \"power encounters\", \"from\": 4751, \"to\": 4767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Regrettably, it seems that many in the West today are unwittingly inviting the return of these ancient pagan gods to once again preside over their societies.\", \"from\": 4770, \"to\": 4927, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4813}, {\"ngram\": \"the return\", \"from\": 4845, \"to\": 4855}, {\"ngram\": \"these ancient pagan gods\", \"from\": 4859, \"to\": 4883}, {\"ngram\": \"their societies\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4926}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This resurgence threatens to undo the profound spiritual and cultural victories achieved by early Christians, reintroducing paganism where the light of Christ once shone brightest.\", \"from\": 4928, \"to\": 5108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5020, \"end\": 5036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2117590046881695e-16, \"text\": \"early Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This resurgence\", \"from\": 4928, \"to\": 4943}, {\"ngram\": \"the profound spiritual and cultural victories\", \"from\": 4962, \"to\": 5007}, {\"ngram\": \"reintroducing paganism\", \"from\": 5038, \"to\": 5060}, {\"ngram\": \"the light\", \"from\": 5067, \"to\": 5076}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 5080, \"to\": 5086}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What can Christ followers do?\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5139, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christ followers\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5135}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christ followers can make a lasting impact by faithfully building strong churches, discipling biological and spiritual children to establish enduring generational legacies, and developing parent-controlled educational systems and schools.\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5379, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christ followers\", \"from\": 5141, \"to\": 5157}, {\"ngram\": \"a lasting impact\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5183}, {\"ngram\": \"strong churches\", \"from\": 5207, \"to\": 5222}, {\"ngram\": \"biological and spiritual children\", \"from\": 5235, \"to\": 5268}, {\"ngram\": \"enduring generational legacies\", \"from\": 5282, \"to\": 5312}, {\"ngram\": \"parent-controlled educational systems\", \"from\": 5329, \"to\": 5366}, {\"ngram\": \"schools\", \"from\": 5371, \"to\": 5378}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, by consistently proclaiming the gospel of Christ to our neighbors, we can ensure that our faith continues to flourish.\", \"from\": 5380, \"to\": 5504, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gospel\", \"from\": 5414, \"to\": 5424}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5434}, {\"ngram\": \"our neighbors\", \"from\": 5438, \"to\": 5451}, {\"ngram\": \"our faith\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5481}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, we should pray for and seek the welfare of our cities and nations (Jeremiah 29:7), love our neighbors as ourselves (Matthew 22:37-40), and have a generational plan to serve our communities.\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5705, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the welfare\", \"from\": 5544, \"to\": 5555}, {\"ngram\": \"our cities\", \"from\": 5559, \"to\": 5569}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 5574, \"to\": 5581}, {\"ngram\": \"Jeremiah\", \"from\": 5583, \"to\": 5591}, {\"ngram\": \"our neighbors\", \"from\": 5604, \"to\": 5617}, {\"ngram\": \"Matthew\", \"from\": 5632, \"to\": 5639}, {\"ngram\": \"a generational plan\", \"from\": 5660, \"to\": 5679}, {\"ngram\": \"our communities\", \"from\": 5689, \"to\": 5704}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This includes raising up exceptional community leaders, business innovators, political figures, educators, historians, artists, composers, scientists, and problem solvers with a Christian worldview.\", \"from\": 5706, \"to\": 5904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5884, \"end\": 5903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_worldview\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian worldview\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_worldview\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_worldview\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"exceptional community leaders\", \"from\": 5731, \"to\": 5760}, {\"ngram\": \"business innovators\", \"from\": 5762, \"to\": 5781}, {\"ngram\": \"political figures\", \"from\": 5783, \"to\": 5800}, {\"ngram\": \"educators\", \"from\": 5802, \"to\": 5811}, {\"ngram\": \"historians\", \"from\": 5813, \"to\": 5823}, {\"ngram\": \"artists\", \"from\": 5825, \"to\": 5832}, {\"ngram\": \"composers\", \"from\": 5834, \"to\": 5843}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 5845, \"to\": 5855}, {\"ngram\": \"problem solvers\", \"from\": 5861, \"to\": 5876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As followers of Christ, we have a creative advantage over non-Christians since we are connected to Jesus, the mastermind who created the universe (John 1:3,12; Ephesians 1:22-23).\", \"from\": 5906, \"to\": 6085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6005, \"end\": 6010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999951208884226, \"rank\": 4.879135218765264e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 6053, \"end\": 6059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_1\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John 1\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_1\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_1\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"followers\", \"from\": 5909, \"to\": 5918}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 5922, \"to\": 5928}, {\"ngram\": \"a creative advantage\", \"from\": 5938, \"to\": 5958}, {\"ngram\": \"Christians\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 5978}, {\"ngram\": \"the mastermind\", \"from\": 6012, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"the universe\", \"from\": 6039, \"to\": 6051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, by cultivating an intimate relationship with God through Jesus Christ and regularly celebrating the Lord's Supper, we signify our commitment to restoring the world to the Father.\", \"from\": 6087, \"to\": 6274, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6153, \"end\": 6165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999966699107031, \"rank\": 3.3301001811237196e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an intimate relationship\", \"from\": 6111, \"to\": 6135}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 6141, \"to\": 6144}, {\"ngram\": \"the Lord's Supper\", \"from\": 6192, \"to\": 6209}, {\"ngram\": \"our commitment\", \"from\": 6222, \"to\": 6236}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 6250, \"to\": 6259}, {\"ngram\": \"the Father\", \"from\": 6263, \"to\": 6273}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This aligns with Jesus' instruction in the Lord's Prayer: \\\"Thy will be done, thy kingdom come, on earth as it is in heaven\\\" (Matthew 6:9-10).\", \"from\": 6275, \"to\": 6416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6292, \"end\": 6297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999951208884226, \"rank\": 4.879135218765264e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This aligns\", \"from\": 6275, \"to\": 6286}, {\"ngram\": \"the Lord's Prayer\", \"from\": 6314, \"to\": 6331}, {\"ngram\": \"Thy\", \"from\": 6334, \"to\": 6337}, {\"ngram\": \"thy kingdom\", \"from\": 6352, \"to\": 6363}, {\"ngram\": \"earth\", \"from\": 6373, \"to\": 6378}, {\"ngram\": \"heaven\", \"from\": 6391, \"to\": 6397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By embodying these principles, we actively participate in God's transformative work.\", \"from\": 6418, \"to\": 6502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these principles\", \"from\": 6431, \"to\": 6447}, {\"ngram\": \"God's transformative work\", \"from\": 6476, \"to\": 6501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dr. Joseph Mattera is an internationally-known author, consultant, and theologian whose mission is to influence leaders who influence culture.\", \"from\": 6506, \"to\": 6648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6510, \"end\": 6516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 